properties.headline: Fire Weather Watch issued January 31 at 2:53PM CST until February 1 at 7:00PM CST by NWS North Platte NE
properties.description:
...CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS POSSIBLE SATURDAY AFTERNOON...

.Abnormally warm temperatures Saturday with daytime highs climbing
into the upper 60s are expected across portions of southwest and
western Nebraska. As these temperatures rise, humidity values will
fall near to slightly below critical levels by the middle of the
afternoon. Strong westerly winds will develop with gusts of up to
25 mph expected for much of western Nebraska and gusts possibly
exceeding 30 mph across the eastern Panhandle and far western
Sandhills. This combination of warm temperatures, dry conditions,
and gusty winds along with cured fuels will potentially produce
critical fire weather conditions. Any fire starts will have
the potential for rapid fire growth in the watch area.

The National Weather Service in North Platte has issued a Fire
Weather Watch FOR wind and low relative humidity, which is in
effect from Saturday morning through Saturday afternoon.

* Affected Area...In NEZ204...Fire Weather Zone 204 Eastern
Panhandle/Crescent Lake NWR. In NEZ210...Fire Weather Zone 210
Frenchman Basin.

* Winds...West 15 to 20 mph with gusts up to 35 mph.

* Relative Humidity...Around 20 percent.

* Temperatures...In the upper 50s.

* Impacts...Any fires that develop have a high potential to spread
rapidly.
properties.instruction:
A Fire Weather Watch means that critical fire weather conditions
are forecast to occur. Listen for later forecasts and possible
Red Flag Warnings.

NWSheadline: FIRE WEATHER WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON FOR POTENTIALLY CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS FOR PORTIONS OF SOUTHWEST THROUGH WESTERN NEBRASKA
